steps.Name: Add Picklist Values
steps.Instruction: These upgrade steps are adding new picklist values to existing objects/fields

steps.Name: Add Picklist Value to the Claim Line Item Object
Manage Picklist Values in Status Field of Claim Line Item Object
steps.Instruction:
You must deactivate the following values in the Status picklist in the Claim Line Item Object:

  • Reopened
  • Pending Approval
  • Approved
  • Pending Payment
  • Payment Approved

Here's how:

  1. Click Check Result to open the Object Manager in a new tab.
  2. In the Quick Find box, enter Claim.
  3. Click Claim Line Item to open it.
  4. Click Fields & Relationships.
  5. Click Status.
  6. Scroll down to the Values section.
  7. Deactivate the following values by clicking Deactivate and then OK:
  • Reopened
  • Pending Approval
  • Approved
  • Pending Payment
  • Payment Approved


In addition, you must set the default value of this picklist to New. Here's how:

  1. Click Check Result to open the Object Manager in a new tab.
  2. In the Quick Find box, enter Claim.
  3. Click Claim Line Item to open it.
  4. Click Status.
  5. In the Values section, click Edit next to the value of New.
  6. Select the Default check box.
  7. Click Save.


The Claim LineItem's Record Type's Status must also be updated.

  1. Click Check Result to open the Object Manager in a new tab.
  2. In the Quick Find box, enter Claim.
  3. Click Claim Line Item to open it.
  4. Click Record Types
  5. Under the Record Type Label, click Claim Line Item
  6. Beside the Status, click Edit
  7. Add all the Available Values to the Selected Values side, except for the ones meant to be deactivated.
  8. In the dropdown marked Default, select New
  9. Save

Add Picklist Value to the Status Field in the Asset Object
steps.Instruction:
You need to add the following picklist values to the Status Picklist on the Asset object:

  • Active
  • Pending Lapse
  • Lapsed

Here's how:

  1. Click Check result to open the Object Manager in a new tab.
  2. In the Values section, click New.
  3. Enter Active, Pending Lapse and Lapsed into the big text field.
  4. Don't select any of the record types below the text field.
  5. Click Save.

steps.Name: Add Fields to Object Field Sets
Add Product Child Item Sequence Field to Quote Detail Field Set
steps.Instruction:
You need to add Product Child Item Sequence field to the Quote Detail Field Set on the Quote Line Item object. Here's how:

  1. Click Check result to open the Object Manager to the Quote Line Item object in a new tab.
  2. On the Field Sets tab, click Quote Detail. 
  3. From the top panel, find Product Child Item Sequence. Drag and drop it into the In the Field Set list on the lower panel.
  4. Click Save

steps.Name: Add Social Security Number Field to Editable Table Field Set
steps.Instruction:
You need to add the Social Security Number field to the Editable Table field set on the Census Members object. Here's how:

  1. Click Check result to open the Object Manager in a new tab.
  2. Search for the Census Member object, then click that object.
  3. Click on the Field Set link on the right panel, then click Editable Table.  
  4. From the top panel, find Social Security Number, drag and drop it into the In the Field Set list on the lower panel.
  5. Click Save.

steps.Name: Add Product Class Fields to Product Field Sets
steps.Instruction:
Add the Parent Class and Parent Class Code fields to the multiple field sets on the Product object. Here's how:

  1. Click Check result to open the Product Field Sets in a new tab.
  2. Click Insurance Plan Selection.
  3. In the top panel, find Parent Class and Parent Class Code. Drag and drop it into the the Field Set list in the lower panel titled In the Field Set.
  4. Click Save.
  5. Repeat step 2-4 for the follwowing Field Sets: Get Product Spec, QuoteDetail, EligibleProductFields, FieldsAvailableInRating, FieldsAvailableInRules.

steps.Name: Miscellaneous
Add Help Text to the Rating Procedure Name Field  in the Product Object
steps.Instruction:
You need to add help text to the Rating Procedure Name field on the Product object. Here's how:

  1. Click Check result to open the Object Manager to the Product object in a new tab.
  2. Find the Rating Procedure Name field and click on it.
  3. Click Edit.
  4. Enter the following text: If Rating Procedure Type is calculation procedure, fill in the calculation procedure name. If Rating Procedure Type is Integration Procedure, fill in the Integration Procedure's Type_Subtype.
  5. Click Save.

steps.Name: Change Custom Images for Vlocity Custom Object Tabs
steps.Instruction:
Custom images do not get automatically updated on Vlocity custom object tabs. You can update these images manually. Here’s how:

  1. Click Check result to open the Custom Tabs in a new tab.
  2. Find a Vlocity custom object, such as Vlocity Calculation Procedures. Click its name.
  3. Click Edit.
  4. Click Tab Style.
  5. Click Create your own style.
  6. Click Insert an Image.
  7. Choose CalculationProcedures@2x_grey.
  8. Click Save.
  9. Repeat steps 2-7 for all Vlocity custom objects. In step 7 for each object, choose Name_@2xgrey.

steps.Name: Add Picklist Value to the LineOfBusiness Field in the Product2 Object
Add Fields to Claim Line Item Field Sets
steps.Instruction:
You must add these fields in the following field sets on the Claim Line Item object:

  • Claim Item Detail - Created Date, Payee Party Id, Status
  • Expense Item Detail - Created Date, Status
  • New Claim Item - Adjusted Amount, Status

Here's how:

  1. Click Check Result to open the Object Manager in a new tab.
  2. Find the Claim Line Item and click it.
  3. Click Field Sets.
  4. Click Claim Item Detail.
  5. In the Claim Item Detail section, find the following fields and drag and drop them into the lower section:
    1. Created Date
    2. Payee Party Id
    3. Status
  6. Click Save.
  7. Click Field Sets.
  8. Click Expense Item Detail.
  9. In the Expense Item Detail section, find the following field and drag and drop them into the lower section:
    1. Created Date
    2. Status
  10. Click Save.
  11. Click Field Sets.
  12. Click New Claim Item.
  13. In the New Claim Item section, find the following field and drag and drop them into the lower section:
    1. Adjusted Amount
    2. Status
  14. Click Save.
